-\n|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.9139&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.9139.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.9139|title=Top 100 Hit Tracks of 1990|work=RPM|publisher=Library and Archives Canada|accessdate=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|96\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (1991)\n!Position\n|-\n|Australia (ARIA)<ref>{{cite book|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|title=Australia's Music Charts 1988\u20132010|year=2011|publisher=Moonlight Publishing|location=Mt. Martha, VIC, Australia|edition=pdf|page=187}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|59\n|-\n|Canada Top Singles (''RPM'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.2024&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.2024.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.2024|title=RPM Hit Tracks of 1991|work=RPM|publisher=Library and Archives Canada|accessdate=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|53\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web |url=http://longboredsurfer.com/charts.php?year=1991 |title=Billboard Top 100 \u2013 1991 |accessdate=2009-09-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090707155835/http://longboredsurfer.com/charts.php?year=1991 |archivedate=7 July 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|95\n|}\n\n===Certifications===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Australia|type=single|artist=George Michael|title=Freedom! '90|award=Platinum|relyear=1990|certyear=2017|accessdate=4 January 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=George Michael|title=Freedom|award=Silver|relyear=1990|certyear=2019|accessdate=4 January 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|artist=George Michael|title=Freedom|award=Gold|relyear=1990|certyear=1991|accessdate=4 January 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true|streaming=true}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Uses in media==\n{{sources|section|date=January 2019}}\n* It was used at the very end of the 2007 film ''[[I Now Pronounce You Chuck and Larry]]'' as it was sung by actor [[Peter Dante]].\n* It was used in trailers for the film [[Bee Movie]].\n* It was used in the trailer for the film ''[[Keanu (film)|Keanu]]''.\n* It was featured in the [[Pilot (Arrested Development)|pilot episode]] of the television series ''[[Pilot (Arrested Development)|Arrested Development]]''.\n* It was performed as a lip sync song by [[Zachary Quinto]] in the show ''[[Lip Sync Battle]]'' with Cindy Crawford recreating her bathtub scene from the video.<ref>{{Citation|last=Lip Sync Battle on Spike|title=Zachary Quinto performs George Michael's \"Freedom! '90\" (with Cindy Crawford) {{!}} Lip Sync Battle|date=2016-06-10|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TROfag5mSFE|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref>\n*It was performed in 2017 by Anna Kendrick as \"Beca Mitchell\" featuring The Barden Bellas in the movie [[Pitch Perfect 3]].\n*\u201dThe Gang\u201d performs a dance number to it in the [[It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia|It\u2019s Always Sunny in Philadelphia]] season 7 episode \u201cThe High School Reunion Part 2: The Gang\u2019s Revenge\u201d.\n*The song appears in [[T-Mobile]]\u2019s 2019 \u201cWe\u2019re With You\u201d commercial.\n\n==Robbie Williams version==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Freedom\n| cover      = Robbie Williams-Freedom s.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Robbie Williams]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 12 August 1996\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single|CD]]|[[cassette single|cassette]]}}\n| recorded   = 1996\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = 4:20\n| label      = [[Chrysalis Records|Chrysalis]]\n| writer     = George Michael\n| producer   = [[Stephen Hague]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Old Before I Die]]\n| next_year  = 1997\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|eZ05LV-EKYs|\"Freedom\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"Freedom\" was covered in 1996 by [[Robbie Williams]] who released it as his debut single after leaving [[Take That]]. It reached number 2 in the UK, 26 places higher than George Michael's original, and had not been included on any of his albums until 2010, when it was included on Williams' greatest hits album ''[[In and Out of Consciousness: Greatest Hits 1990\u20132010]]''. The single had sold 280,000 copies by the end of 1996, being certified Silver by the [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/platinum/platinumright.asp?rq=search_plat&r_id=21774|title=\"Freedom\" Silver Certification|publisher=British Phonographic Industry}}</ref> Williams had left Take That the previous year and therefore could identify himself with much of the sentiment in the song, although he did not use the line ''\"we had every bigshot goodtime band on the run boy, we were living in a fantasy\"'' in his version.\n\nThe music video shows Williams dancing in the sea and in a field, celebrating his separation from his former group. Williams later said that the song had not even been recorded by the scheduled date of filming and instead mimed to Michael's version of the song.{{cn|date=January 2019}}\n\n===Track listings===\n'''UK CD1'''\n# \"Freedom\"\n# \"Freedom\" (Arthur Baker Mix)\n# \"Freedom\" (Instrumental)\n# \"Interview \u2013 Part One\"\n\n'''UK CD2'''\n# \"Freedom\" (radio edit)\n# \"Freedom\" (The Next Big Genn Mix)\n# \"Freedom\" (Arthur Baker's Shake And Bake Mix)\n# \"Interview \u2013 Part Two\"\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1996)\n!Peak<br/>positions<ref>{{cite web|url=http://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Robbie+Williams&titel=Freedom&cat=s|title=australian-charts.com - Robbie Williams - Freedom|first=Steffen|last=Hung|website=australian-charts.com}}</ref>\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|6|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|19|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|16|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|16|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Finland|7|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|10|songid=3269|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|6|song=Freedom|accessdate=11 May 2018|refname=ire2}}\n|-\n|Italy (Hit Parade Italia)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitparadeitalia.it/indici/per_interprete/aw.htm|title=Indice per Interprete: W|language=Italian|accessdate=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch40|10|year=1996|week=33|accessdate=11 May 2018|refname=dut402}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|12|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|39|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|1|date=19960810|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|- \n|Spain ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|AFYVE]])<ref>{{cite book|title=S\u00f3lo \u00e9xitos: a\u00f1o a a\u00f1o, 1959\u20132002|last=Salaverri|first=Fernando|date=September 2005|publisher=Fundaci\u00f3n Autor-SGAE|isbn=84-8048-639-2|edition=1st|location=Spain}}</ref> \n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|24|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|8|song=Freedom|artist=Robbie Williams|accessdate=11 May 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|2|date=19960810|accessdate=11 May 2018|refname=\"UKRobbieWilliams\"}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{George Michael singles}}\n{{Robbie Williams singles}}\n\n[[Category:George Michael songs]]\n[[Category:1990 singles]]\n[[Category:1996 debut singles]]\n[[Category:Robbie Williams songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written 